Your Honor,

I, Charlotte Porter, appear before you today as the defendant, fully acknowledging and pleading guilty to the charge of careless driving. I deeply regret my actions on that fateful day, where I displayed irresponsible behavior by driving aggressively and at a higher speed than permitted. Additionally, I made the reckless decision to answer a text message while operating a vehicle, which led to the unfortunate consequence of crashing into a guardrail. Although the outcome did not result in harm to anyone but myself, I am acutely aware of the potential danger I could have inflicted upon others sharing the road.

I am compelled to stress to the Court that my guilty plea signifies genuine remorse and a sincere acceptance of accountability. This collision has prompted deep reflection, making me fully comprehend the dangerous nature of my actions. It acts as a vivid reminder of the utmost importance of responsible driving and the potential consequences that arise from distracted and aggressive behavior.

In considering the circumstances of my case, I would like to bring certain factors to the Court's attention. At the age of 37, I have maintained an otherwise clean driving record, demonstrating my commitment to safe and lawful driving practices. Furthermore, I actively contribute to the British Heart Foundation through regular donations, showcasing my dedication to bettering the community and promoting the wellbeing of others.

I am aware that a prior violation resulted in the addition of 3 penalty points towards my license for speeding. I acknowledge the weight this violation carries and take full responsibility for my actions. However, I firmly believe that my genuine guilty plea, coupled with my profound remorse and sincere commitment to personal growth, should be considered as a significant mitigating factor. I accept the consequences of my mistakes and earnestly hope that the Court will recognize my plea, along with the steps I have taken and will continue to take, as a testament to my dedication to ensuring the safety of myself and others on the road.

Thank you, Your Honor, for your kind consideration of my case.

