NEW STATEMENT:

1249
Your Honor,

I, Charlotte Porter, humbly come before you today as the defendant, wholeheartedly accepting my guilt and pleading guilty to the charge of careless driving. I am profoundly remorseful for my actions on that ill-fated day, where I exhibited reckless behavior by driving aggressively and exceeding the permitted speed limit. Additionally, I made the irresponsible choice to respond to a text message while operating a vehicle, resulting in the unfortunate outcome of colliding with a guardrail. Although I was fortunate that no one else was harmed, I am acutely aware of the potential danger I posed to others sharing the road.

I wish to emphasize the sincere depth of my remorse and my unwavering acceptance of accountability. This collision has prompted an introspective journey that has made me vividly understand the grave consequences of distracted and aggressive driving. I am dedicated to ensuring that this realization leads to personal growth and a renewed commitment to responsible driving practices.

In light of my case, I would like to bring certain factors to the Court's attention. As a 37-year-old individual, I have diligently maintained an otherwise clean driving record, exemplifying my commitment to safe and lawful driving habits. Additionally, I make regular donations to the British Heart Foundation, demonstrating my sincere dedication to the betterment of the community and the well-being of others.

While I acknowledge the imposition of 3 penalty points for a previous speeding violation on my license, I believe it is important to recognize the significant impact that my genuine guilty plea and profound remorse have on the present case. I am deeply remorseful for my actions and the potential harm I could have caused not only to myself but to everyone around me on the road.

Thank you, Your Honor, for your thoughtful consideration of my case.

